flowRoot.flowPara: > Open education can be understood as education based on open educational resources, but also as accessible education that reduces barriers (distance, costs, etc.).
> The digital world is full of open-access knowledge, and many people benefit from open education in their activities such as IT professionals with tutorials, forums and so on.
> The boundary between open and non-open education is sometimes difficult to define, and can arise around a multitude of resources and contexts. It can be seen as omnipresent.
Educational content that can be freely used, modified and shared, enabling a whole range of open and decentralised collaborative practices with a variety of pedagogical approaches.
Open educational resources are all forms of freely accessible educational content, which may be under an open licence but not necessarily, the legal aspects being not always mastered.
It can be a PowerPoint, a textbook, a publication on social media, a blog or many other types of more or less complex documents. Whether it's text, images, video or audio...

Encyclopaedias, from Diderot's 1751 encyclopaedia during the Age of Enlightenment to Wikipedia, were designed to bring together knowledge that would influence our education. Wikipedia's content is produced collaboratively, under a creative commons (BY-SA) licence. It is one of the most notable open education projects in history.

This whole educational environment around open models is open education. It is based on open educational resources that can be reused, coupled with pedagogical strategies to help in the appropriation of these concepts.

flowRoot.flowPara: Around these open educational resources an infinite number of pedagogical practices can be articulated to improve learning, whether in the way these resources are constructed, or the way they are mobilised in relation to their environment... the whole complexity of pedagogy! With the emergence of the digital and these dynamics of openness, new practices are being invented, for example in the way learners and trainers interact.
